{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_bullock_ver01/data/sn82016181/00516999603/1937100501/1149.xml":{"full_text":"John L. Lewis Outlines His Political Aims\nBy United Press\nNEW YORK, Oct. 5\u2014In a savage counter attack on\nWilliam Green, American Federation of Labor presi\ndent, John L. Lewis, chairman of the Committee for\nIndustrial Organization, renounced all personal po\nlitical ambitions.\nAddressing 12,000 members of unions*\naffiliated with the C. I. O. in Madi\nson Square Garden last night, Lewis\nsaid his political ambitions were sole\nly (1) the election of Thomas Ken\nnedy, an official of Lewis\u2019 United\nMine Workers, as Governor of Penn\nsylvania; (2) a C. I. O. victory in\ntoday's municipal elections in De\ntroit; (3) the re-election of Mayor\nF. H. LaGuardia here, and (4) the\ngrowth of the American Labor Party\ninto a major party.\nA \u2018POLITICAL WHEEZE\u2019\nGreen, he said, was a \u201c7-year-old\nboy defying his parents.\u201d\nHe was\nemploying a \u201cpolitical wheeze\u201d to in\nsure his re-election as president of\nthe A. F. of L.\n\u201cWhen he says the A. F. of L. will\nform a fighting machine to crush\nand destroy the C. I. O\u201e just how\nwould that be done?\u201d Lewis said.\n\u201cDo they mean they will resort to\nforce? The use of fists, of clubs or\narms?\nA CIVIL WAR? i\n\u201cSurely the mild Mr. Green is not,\ngoing to declare a civil war in Amer-1\nica. He might be charged with\ndisturbing the peace.\u201d\ni\nGreen\u2019s Drive to Crush\nC. 1.0. Unions Is Slowed\nDENVER, Oct. 5\u2014The American\nFederation of Labor convention today1\ndeveloped into bitter conflicts arising\nfrom demands for expulsion of rebel\nCommittee for Industrial Organiza- I\ntion unions and for abolishment of\nthe National Labor Relations Board.\nPress \u2018Gag\u2019 Bill Is Passed\nby Alberta Legislature\nBy United Press I\nEDMONTON, Alta., Oct. 5\u2014The Al\nberta legislature approved the gov-1\nernment\u2019s drastic press and bank\ncontrol measures early tody.\nThe press bill establishes a virtual\ngovernment dictatorship over the\nprovince\u2019s daily and weekly news\npapers. It will compel Alberta news\npapers to reveal the sources of any\nnews questioned by the government\nand to prin*- any statement issued by\nthe government press bureau.\nChrysler Enlarges Plant\nMONTREAL, Oct. 5\u2014The Chrysler\nCorp. of Canada will spend nearly\n$4,000,000 on new construction already\nstarted at its Windsor plant, John C.\nMcGuire. sales manager for Canada,\nannounced here. Decision to expand\nwas based on better sales prospects,\nMcGuire said, and on an improved\ngeneral business outlook in Canada.\non\nStudents Paint\nMellon I nstitute\n'After Grid Game\nBy United Press\nOct. 5\u2014Angelo\nPITTSBURGH,\nRubino, New York University\nlaw instructor, was en route home\ntoday, free of charges of \u201cmalicious\nmischief.\u201d\nHe was arrested early\nyesterday after students painted a\nfootball victory score on the $6,000,\n000 Mellon Institute building.\nHe was released after spending\nthe day in jail in default of $1000\nbail.\nPolice reported New York\nUniversity agreed to pay costs of\nremoving the paint.\n\u201cN. Y. U. 18\u2014C. T. 14.\u201d read the\n6-foot letters. It was the score by\nwhich N. Y. U. defeated Carnegie\nTech Saturday. The building was\ndonated to science by the late\nRichard B. and Andrew W. Mellon.\nIt is Grecian in architecture, with\n62 five-story monolithic columns\nrunning the length of all four sides.\nis your\nLUCKY\nNUMBER\nYour Lucky\nNumber for\nExpert Floral Service\nis District 1300\nBy\n1\na of H Street\nAS NEAR AS YOUR PHONE\nNot Guilty Plea Entered\nin Detroit Murder of 2\nDETROIT, Oct. 5\u2014William Haw\nthorne, 23-year-old policeman who J\nconfessed killing his wife and her1\nfriend John M. Barrett, 23, stood\nmute late yesterday on arraignment.\nA plea of not guilty was entered.\nHawthorne's attorney, indicated be\nlief Hawthorne was \u201cmentally ill\"\nwhen he entered Barrett's home and\nkilled his wife and Barrett.\nMine Workers Journal\nScores A. F. of L \u2018Snub\u2019\nThe United Mine Workers Journal,\nspokesman for the biggest C. I. O.\nunion, today attacked what it called\na \u201cdirty snub\" of the Roosevelt Ad-\nministration by tire A. F. of L.\n\u201cJust to show how spiteful it can\nbe,\" The Journal said, the federation\nhas \u201csnubbed the Roosevelt Adminis\ntration\" by not inviting Secretary of\nLabor Perkins to speak at the current\nA. F. of L. convention in Denver.\n\u201cThis snub is administered by the\nlittle group of harebrained individuals\nwho run the federation and who\ndon\u2019t like the President, Secretary\nPerkins or the Administration,\u201d it\nadded.\nNorris at Mayo Clinic\nROCHESTER. Minn. Oct. 5 Mayo\nClinic officials attended Sen. George\nW. Norris (Ind., Neb? at Kahler Hos\npital today. Hospital attendants said\nthe Senator. who retired to a sum\nmer home this summer for a rest,\ncame to Rochester merely for medical\nexamination. He is not seriously ill,\nthey said.\nLEATHER\nG W KING. JR\nSil 11th Si. N W\nGOODs\n*z\ny9\n1\nPs\n2\nh\nEXPERT\nWATCII\nREPAIRS!\n\nEASY\nTERMS\nOnly finest parts used!\nAll work guaranteed!\nSurprisingly low prices!\nS.&N.Katz\n1114 F ST. N. W.\nQuality Jewelers for 32 Yaarif\nJPIN\nWoodward LOTHROD\n10th 11th F and G Streets\nPHONE DISTRICT 5300\nReoCAoss\nSpecial Low Prices\nWestinghouse\nWASHERS\nIRONERS\n299TSWWTRTC\n60\n2*9\n7A\n\nShown Above\u2014\nDe Luxe Washer\nNine pounds of clothes per load. The tub\nand motor are cushioned in rubber and the j\nwringer has many safety and easy operat\ning features. Strikingly finished in gleam\ning white with black trim. The low price\nmakes this an exceptional buy at this time.\nDo your own laundry work and save on\nlaundry bills and on clothes replacement\ncosts. And have more clean linens and\nclothes on hand at all times with a smaller\ninvestment\n\nELECTRIC APPLIANCES, FIFTH F100m\nShown Below\u2014\nCabinet Ironer\nDivided heating elements, each serving\none-half of the ironing shoe and each with\nits own thermostatic control, enables the\nuser to select the desired temperature for\neach end of the roll. Cabinet top when\nclosed serves as a useful working surface\nin kitchen or laundry. When open and in\nuse it serves as a convenient shelf for\nironed articles.\nThe ironer is finished in\ngleaming white with black trim.\n1\n\ni\n5\n-A\nj todtw* 0\nada\ni\nli\n\nlet\n4\n69s\n\nt\nJ\nY\nl\nW i\n^Deferred payments may be arranged\nfor a slight additional carrying charge.","height":"21184","width":"14612"}}
